## Part 6: Data Flow Example: Creating and Running a Pod

### Complete Request/Response Flow

```
1. KUBELET INITIATES POD CREATION
   └─ pkg/kubelet/kuberuntime/kuberuntime_manager.go
      └─ runtimeService.RunPodSandbox(ctx, config, handler)

2. gRPC CLIENT SEND
   └─ staging/src/k8s.io/cri-client/pkg/remote_runtime.go
      └─ Calls remoteRuntimeService.RunPodSandbox()
         └─ Marshals request to protobuf
         └─ Sends gRPC call to containerd socket

3. gRPC SERVER RECEIVE (containerd)
   └─ plugins/cri/cri.go: criGRPCServer
      └─ instrument/instrumented_service.go: instrumentedService (wraps)
         └─ internal/cri/server/service.go: criService.RunPodSandbox() (implementation)

4. CONTAINERD PROCESSING
   └─ Receives: runtime.RunPodSandboxRequest
      ├─ Extract config
      ├─ Generate sandbox ID
      ├─ Reserve name
      ├─ Setup CNI network
      ├─ Create containerd container
      ├─ Start task
      └─ Store in sandboxStore

5. gRPC RESPONSE SEND
   └─ Return: runtime.RunPodSandboxResponse{PodSandboxId: id}
      └─ Marshal to protobuf
      └─ Send over gRPC

6. KUBELET RECEIVE
   └─ Unmarshals response
   └─ Stores sandbox ID for future container operations
   └─ Proceeds with container creation
```

